  "title": "CARPENTER",
  "description": "<ol><li>Read and interpret blueprints, sketches, and construction plans to determine the scope of work and required materials.</li><li>Measure, cut, and shape wood or other materials accurately, using hand and power tools, to build or repair structures such as walls, floors, doors, windows, and cabinetry.</li><li>Install structures, including framing, walls, partitions, and roofing systems, ensuring proper alignment, fit, and adherence to building codes and safety regulations.</li><li>Construct and install interior and exterior finishes, including trims, moldings, casings, doors, and windows for a polished and professional appearance.</li><li>Interpreting blueprints and drawing up plans to determine materials required and a plan of action.</li><li>Measuring, cutting, shaping, and smoothing lumber and other construction materials.</li><li>Constructing building frameworks including walls, floors, and doorframes.</li><li>Ensuring structures are level, square, and securely assembled.</li><li>Installing features such as doors, cabinets, stairs, and paneling.</li><li>Inspecting and replacing damaged frameworks or other structures and fixtures.</li><li>Managing construction materials, tools, and equipment.</li><li>Maintaining a safe and clean work environment by adhering to safety and health regulations.</li></ol>",
